      Parameters:

    • isElementVisible

      public boolean isElementVisible(String locator, int timeoutInSeconds)
      Determines if the specified element is visible. An element can be rendered invisible by setting the CSS "visibility" property to "hidden", or the "display" property to "none", either for the element itself or one if its ancestors. This method will fail if the element is not present.

      locator - an element locator
      timeoutInSeconds - int time value
      Returns:
      true if the specified element is visible, false otherwise

      public String selectLikeItemFromDropDown(String locator, String stringLike)
      selects an item from a dropdown list that contains the parameter stringLike
      Parameters:
      locator - - identifies the dropdown list
      stringLike - - string to match in the elements of the dropdown list
      Returns:

    • selectItemFromDropDown

      public void selectItemFromDropDown(String locator, String value)
      selects the correct item from the given select item in the GUI. If the value is not set (null or "") this method does nothing, else it will try to select the item.

      If the value does not contain 'label=' it is added automatically.

    • selectItemFromDropDown

      public void selectItemFromDropDown(String locator, String item, boolean isRequired)
      if dropdown is a required field, will select from the list, depending on content of parameter item if item is empty, selects random element from the dropdown list if item has content, selects it from the dropdown list if dropdown isn't required field, does nothing
      Parameters:
      locator - - identifies the dropdown list
      item - - element to select on the dropdown list
      isRequired - - is this a required field

    • selectItemStartWithFromDropDown

      public void selectItemStartWithFromDropDown(String locator, String startsWith)
      selects an item from a dropdown list that starts with the parameter stringStartsWith
      Parameters:
      locator - - identifies the dropdown list
      startsWith - - string to match starts with in elements of the dropdown list
